step.reason:
\begin{align}
  \ora{AB}&=\ora{B}-\ora{A}=\vector{2}{3}{2} \\
  \ora{AC}&=\ora{C}-\ora{A}=\vector{-4}{0}{4}
\end{align} \\
%text
Since $\ora{AB}$ and $\ora{AC}$ are along the plane, the 
normal to the plane must be the vector cross 
product of these two. Therefore, 
%
\begin{align}
  \ora{N}&=\ora{AB}\times \ora{AC} \\
    &=\left\vert \begin{array}{ccc}
           \hat\imath & \hat\jmath & \hat{\it k} \\
           2 & 3 & 2 \\
           -4 & 0 & 4
         \end{array}\right\vert
    =\vector{12}{16}{12}
\end{align}
